NHS North West London Integrated Care Board ("NHS NW London ICB" or "ICB") required a Central London (Westminster) based provision of a Dementia Advisor (DA) to deliver post-diagnostic support, information and advice to people with a diagnosis of dementia. The main focus is supporting people with a recent diagnosis, and/or in early stages, to live well with dementia, to help them to stay independent and access services in the community. The DA also remains as point of contact for people with dementia from diagnosis through to end-of-life. The post holder provides information on local support services for the person with dementia, providing advice and signposting as and when required. Even though the main focus for the DA is the person with a diagnosis of dementia (rather than Carers), the DA closely liaises with families and friends of the person with dementia as required. The post holder also takes an active role in the delivery of Westminster Memory Café sessions, raises awareness about dementia in the community, takes an active role in the Dementia Friendly Communities initiative and builds links and relationships to enhance partnership working with other services/organisations across the dementia pathway.

The aims of the service are to offer high quality post-diagnostic support, information and advice to:
Promote an understanding of dementia & manage the symptoms of dementia;
Help people live more independently;
Enable easy access to services, seek out the right support at the right time; 
Feel in control of their life and their future;
Reduce isolation, rebuild their support network;
Better manage their mental & physical health; and
Empower people to live well with dementia.

The Supplier will deliver the 2022-23 to 2025-26 English Housing Surveys.  The Contract will initially cover three survey years (2022-23 to 2024-25), with the option to extend the Contract to cover an additional survey year (2025-26) in accordance with the provisions of set out in the Call-Off Contract.  

In addition to the core English Housing Survey, the Supplier will also be required, over the course of the Contract, to deliver: 

two English Private Landlord Surveys; 

one Market Value Survey;

a methodology to produce local level modelled statistics on housing quality and dwelling condition, produce the first release of those statistics and train analysts in DLUHC to produce the statistics going forward; and 

Social Value and sustainability elements.

Folkestone & Hythe District Council ("the Council") wishes to select and appoint a suitable supplier for construction works at Biggins Wood and invites prospective suppliers to submit a Tender to meet the Council's requirements.

The site of the proposed residential and indutrial/commercial development is located on the derelict plot of land to the south of the M20 motorway approximately 2.2km northwest of Folkestone town centre. The site is accessed from Caesars Way to the east. 

The overall development is ultimately to construct 77 residential dwellings and mixed use development of commercial/office units ( 660 m2) and industrial/storage units (5,142 m2) together with associated car parking, open space, landscaping. This contract forms the initial enabling Works to facilitate the development of the site

The Works in this contract comprise, but is not limited to, the construction of an adoptable access road; 
Ecological works to the satisfaction of the Local Planning Authority;
Tree protection measures;
Stripping the site of vegetation, shrubs and unprotected trees;
Removal of stockpile of construction and demolition materials;
Preparation of Interim Verification report;
Removal of contaminated materials;

The Contract is expected to start on in July 2022.

Interested suppliers can visit the Kent Business Portal (www.kentbusinessportal.org.uk) and search current opportunities for DN614146. To quote you must complete and return the "Invitation to Quote Response Document" via the portal.

